casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellee, v. Crowley, Appellant.

[Cite as State v. Crowley, 99 Ohio St.3d 146, 2003-Ohio-2766.]

(No. 2003-0242 Submitted May 14, 2003 Decided June 11, 2003.) Ron O’Brien, Franklin County Prosecuting Attorney, and Jennifer L. Coriell, Assistant Prosecuting Attorney, for appellee. Donald C. Schumacher, for appellant.

{¶ 1} The judgment of the court of appeals on the sole proposition of law is affirmed on the authority of State v. Fisher, 99 Ohio St.3d 127, 2003-Ohio-2761, 789 N.E.2d 222.

Moyer, C.J., Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer, Lundberg Stratton and O’Con-nor, JJ., concur. Cook, J., not participating.
